Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan and cook until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} each side. While the chicken cooks, trim the @green beans{150%g}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}.

Once browned, pop the chicken onto a #baking tray{} and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes} - set your pan aside for later. When cooked, remove from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the @BBQ sauce{64%g}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water for the sauce{50%ml} into a #small bowl{} and stir together.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Once hot, add the green beans and onion. Stir-fry until the beans start to char and the onion has softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Then add a splash of @water{splash} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. Allow to cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to your plates and drain any excess water.

Pour the BBQ sauce into the (now empty) #pan{}, stir well, then bring back to a bubble and allow to reduce slightly. Add the chicken to the pan and spoon the sauce all over. Serve the BBQ chicken on your plates with the beans and wedges alongside. Spoon any remaining sauce from the pan over the chicken. Enjoy!

> STEP 5 MOD: If you've chosen to add chorizo to your meal, add @?chorizo{60%g}(diced) to the pan before the beans. Fry until it starts to brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. Then add the beans and onion and continue as instructed.